*** GAMS/GUROBI option file for ReEDS
*** Docs: https://www.gams.com/latest/docs/S_GUROBI.html
*** Activate with: model.OptFile = 1;
*** Gurobi is the most direct CPLEX swap-in and is widely used for ReEDS.

*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Algorithm selection
*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Method: -1 auto, 0 primal simplex, 1 dual simplex, 2 barrier,
***         3 concurrent, 4 deterministic concurrent, 5 det. concurrent simplex,
***         6 PDHG (Gurobi 13+)
*** 2 (barrier) is the standard ReEDS recipe and matches cplex.opt lpmethod=4.
Method 2

*** Threads. Default uses all cores; pinning to 8 matches the CPLEX baseline.
Threads 8

*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Time / iteration limits
*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Wall-clock time limit in seconds (2 days, matches cplex.opt)
TimeLimit 172800

*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Tolerances - matched to ReEDS cplex.opt where possible
*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Primal feasibility tolerance (CPLEX eprhs 1e-5)
FeasibilityTol 1e-5

*** Dual feasibility / reduced-cost tolerance (CPLEX epopt 1e-6)
OptimalityTol 1e-6

*** Barrier convergence tolerance (CPLEX barepcomp 1e-8)
BarConvTol 1e-8

*** Markowitz pivot tolerance (CPLEX epmrk; left at default - uncomment to raise)
* MarkowitzTol 0.0078125

*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Preprocessing / scaling
*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Presolve: -1 auto, 0 off, 1 conservative, 2 aggressive
Presolve 2

*** Aggregator passes (CPLEX aggind 5 -> Gurobi uses Aggregate fill)
*** Aggregate: 0 off, 1 on (default), 2 enable extra
Aggregate 1
AggFill 10

*** Scaling: -1 auto, 0 off, 1 standard, 2 aggressive, 3 geometric-mean
ScaleFlag 2

*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Barrier-specific tuning
*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Ordering for the barrier (0 AMD, 1 nested dissection, -1 auto)
BarOrder -1

*** Number of barrier iterations between log lines (and for convergence checks)
BarIterLimit 1000

*** Set BarHomogeneous=1 if barrier reports primal/dual infeasibility on a
*** model you believe to be feasible - improves numerical robustness.
* BarHomogeneous 1

*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Crossover (barrier -> basic solution)
*** Crossover: -1 auto, 0 none, 1 push primal then dual, 2 push dual then primal,
***            3 push primal only, 4 push dual only
*** ReEDS needs basic marginals, so leave crossover on (-1 = auto).
*** To skip crossover for diagnostic speed tests, set Crossover 0.
*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Crossover -1
CrossoverBasis 0

*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Numerical robustness (uncomment if barrier struggles on hard years)
*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** NumericFocus: 0 auto, 1-3 increasing care with numerics (slower but safer)
* NumericFocus 1

*** Use quad-precision arithmetic in simplex when numerics are bad
* Quad 1

*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Logging / IIS
*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Console output: 1 on (default), 0 off
OutputFlag 1

*** Display interval (seconds) for barrier log lines
DisplayInterval 30

*** Compute IIS automatically if the model is infeasible (mirrors cplex.opt iis 1)
IIS 1
